00:29:38.290 --> 00:29:42.740
I'm gonna put a protection around and about them.

00:29:42.740 --> 00:30:02.767
" When I was trying to tell you about Psalm 91 and Psalm 23, this is what I'm trying to tell you: that you've got to prepare yourself for what's about to take place.

00:30:02.767 --> 00:30:08.660
It is dark in Egypt and light in Israel.

00:30:08.660 --> 00:30:10.903
Yeah, it was Goshen.

00:30:11.634 --> 00:30:29.931
I believe with all my heart that we're the representation of that, that we'll be the church without spot or wrinkle rising up with a backbone like a crowbar, being that light in these dark hours.

00:30:31.680 --> 00:30:41.610
And most people are still thinking about me and my four no more with that mentality of thinking, "How am I just going to get barely by to pay my electric, water, and gas?

00:30:44.955 --> 00:30:48.433
" And He said, "Start to stretch yourself to believe for more.

00:30:52.217 --> 00:30:52.446
" And I'm like, "Okay, I can do it.

00:30:52.446 --> 00:30:53.131
Help me.

00:30:53.131 --> 00:30:54.980
I believe; help my unbelief.

00:30:54.980 --> 00:30:56.960
" Diana and I believe; help our unbelief.

00:30:56.960 --> 00:30:58.040
Stretch us.

00:31:15.267 --> 00:31:15.600
I'm asking God to stretch you today to take you to the next level to believe Him for more.

00:31:15.600 --> 00:31:19.742
Now, do you believe all these things are going to happen, Brandon?

00:31:24.528 --> 00:31:24.800
I believe that's what Matthew 24 said.

00:31:24.800 --> 00:31:26.159
Now, is that fear?

00:31:26.159 --> 00:31:26.959
No.

00:31:26.959 --> 00:31:28.159
We're closers.

00:31:29.179 --> 00:31:30.419
We were made for pressure.

00:31:30.419 --> 00:31:33.200
We were built for such a time as this.

00:31:33.200 --> 00:31:34.267
It shouldn't shake us.

00:31:34.267 --> 00:31:34.693
Why?

00:31:48.480 --> 00:31:48.790
Because we've got what it takes.

00:31:59.710 --> 00:32:00.040
We're the closers of the game.

00:32:00.040 --> 00:32:04.346
He saved the best for last.

00:32:04.346 --> 00:32:08.000
Now, your grandma's generation probably couldn't have handled it.

00:32:08.000 --> 00:32:19.680
They'd probably freak out and crawl underneath their bed covers and hide themselves and sit and shake all day.

00:32:19.680 --> 00:32:25.751
But not us because there is some—we've got that oomph, that grit to sit there and say, "Listen, we will not bow.

00:32:25.751 --> 00:32:27.640
We will not burn.

00:32:27.640 --> 00:32:30.880
We will take the land for Jesus.

00:32:30.880 --> 00:32:46.767
We will rise up with a backbone and we will proclaim that Jesus Christ is coming, and He's coming sooner rather than later.

00:32:46.767 --> 00:32:48.399
" He's coming.

00:32:48.788 --> 00:33:12.674
And I believe we're about to see this earth shaken like we've never seen it shaken before with signs and wonders, glorious healings and outpourings of the glory, the demonstrations and the manifestations—not just physical healings, but seeing people delivered of demonic spirits, seeing people raised from the dead, seeing blind eyes opened, ears opened, and the lame—all biblical stuff today.

00:33:12.674 --> 00:33:15.371
I go, "Well, how come we don't see that?

00:33:15.371 --> 00:33:19.659
" I'm believing God for it, and they're seeing it in foreign countries.

00:33:19.659 --> 00:33:26.057
I have people tell me, "Well, Brandon, we see miracles all the time in our church.

00:33:34.720 --> 00:33:35.050
We live over in Africa.

00:33:35.710 --> 00:33:38.983
" The modern culture of America, we don't see it a lot.

00:33:39.447 --> 00:33:40.711
And it's about to change.

00:33:40.711 --> 00:33:42.000
We see certain things.

00:33:42.000 --> 00:33:48.120
You might hear somebody, "Well, I had a headache, brother, and I got healed.

00:33:55.919 --> 00:33:57.538
" I go to Billy Burke's meetings and you see people get healed of really cool stuff.

00:33:57.538 --> 00:34:00.240
But it's not the rule; it's the exception.

00:34:09.679 --> 00:34:09.983
That happens all the time.

00:34:09.983 --> 00:34:12.990
Signs and wonders will follow them that believe.

00:34:17.029 --> 00:34:17.239
And that's what I'm expecting.

00:34:19.946 --> 00:34:31.269
It's not something we go, "Well, every once in a while in the sweet by and by, some sister might get healed of something and we'll hear about it.

00:34:31.269 --> 00:34:54.480
" No, I want it to be so widespread that it takes over our churches and we see it, and people are drawn to it in the world and say, "What are they doing in there?

00:34:54.480 --> 00:35:00.040
" Did you know I heard about 10 people in there that got healed of cancer this last week?

00:35:00.040 --> 00:35:04.459
Send them over there if they have cancer.

00:35:14.320 --> 00:35:20.400
If they've got some kind of diabetes or heart disease, send them over because we know that if they go in there, the power and the glory of the Lord is going to raise them up out of their deathbed.

00:35:20.400 --> 00:35:21.264
Shock and awe.

00:35:21.264 --> 00:35:22.344
We're in the news.

00:35:22.344 --> 00:35:23.250
What is it?

00:35:23.250 --> 00:35:27.989
Did you hear another testimony of somebody getting up from the dead?

00:35:27.989 --> 00:35:32.693
Have you heard about anybody getting up from the dead?

00:35:32.693 --> 00:35:34.187
Not very often.

00:35:47.1000 --> 00:35:48.320
It shouldn't be such a rarity—if ever.

00:35:53.876 --> 00:35:54.178
You go, 'Well, they were in the morgue for a couple of days.

00:35:54.178 --> 00:35:56.960
' Well, I really don't know.

00:35:56.960 --> 00:35:58.453
Is that AI?

00:36:01.350 --> 00:36:05.760
It should just be every day that we walk in the glory of God.

00:36:05.760 --> 00:36:09.280
And it's time to believe Him for bigger.

00:36:09.280 --> 00:36:25.528
He said it, 'Enlarge your capacity to believe Me,' not just for finances but for the demonstrations and manifestations of the glory, entertaining angels unaware, flowing with the gifts of the Spirit.

00:36:25.528 --> 00:36:31.253
Paul and Silas, bound in the prison, started singing.

00:36:31.253 --> 00:36:34.377
The walls began to shake.

00:36:34.377 --> 00:36:35.839
They're set free.

00:36:36.059 --> 00:36:36.939
You go, 'What happened?

00:36:36.939 --> 00:36:37.159
' Look at that!

00:36:46.391 --> 00:36:46.622
I wonder if we could go back in time and sit there and listen to their stories.

00:36:52.044 --> 00:36:52.355
What was their coffee time like in the morning?

00:36:52.355 --> 00:36:56.684
If they all gathered around, what did you see today?

00:36:56.684 --> 00:37:06.800
When they were there talking and they had family time, and they're all sitting around, do you remember when Uncle John went out and did this or that?

00:37:06.800 --> 00:37:09.520
Matthew went and did this or that.

00:37:09.520 --> 00:37:16.160
They're all in there, and we're having dinner together, eating figs or whatever they were doing and hanging out.

00:37:31.784 --> 00:37:32.176
Do you remember that one time we went into the marketplace and we saw that guy get up from the dead?

00:37:36.960 --> 00:37:38.640
I can't even imagine what their conversations were like, sitting there talking about the good old days.

00:37:38.640 --> 00:37:41.432
But it's time for us to have our days.

00:37:41.432 --> 00:37:47.871
I just try to believe Him.

00:37:47.871 --> 00:37:53.680
Stretch out and start to thank Him for what He's about to do in this generation.

00:38:01.460 --> 00:38:09.488
He told me, 'Brandon, I'm going to show up and show off, and I will make Myself known to this generation—that I am not a God of religion and what our grandmas used to tell us about.

00:38:09.488 --> 00:38:12.827
' No, it's time for our turn.

00:38:12.827 --> 00:38:16.608
It's time for this generation.

00:38:20.900 --> 00:38:27.661
He said, 'I'm going to visit this generation one more time with the greatest harvest of souls this world has ever seen before.

00:38:27.661 --> 00:38:31.199
' Brandon, it's time to believe Me for bigger.

00:38:46.639 --> 00:38:47.039
The old wells of revival are coming uncapped.

00:38:47.039 --> 00:38:54.032
Listening to Him, like He said, 'It's a great day to sell silver today.

00:38:54.032 --> 00:38:55.136
' Really?

00:39:11.040 --> 00:39:11.340
Well, that doesn't...

00:39:11.340 --> 00:39:11.940
okay.

00:39:11.940 --> 00:39:19.213
Well, it's a great day to buy some gold today if you could get two grand of it.

00:39:19.213 --> 00:39:24.880
It's a great day just following His voice.

00:39:24.880 --> 00:39:26.613
It's just an example.

00:39:26.613 --> 00:39:30.320
'You see that piece of land over there?

00:39:30.320 --> 00:39:41.669
I don't know why, but if He said it, "Hey, that land right there is only a couple hundred dollars.

00:39:41.669 --> 00:39:54.920
"' You go and you buy it, and the state comes in and says, 'We want to build a highway through here.

00:39:54.920 --> 00:40:01.698
We want to buy it from you for five million dollars.

00:40:01.698 --> 00:40:12.809
' I just know that God is a God that is able to do exceedingly abundantly above all that we dare ask or think.

00:40:12.809 --> 00:40:18.940
And if He can do it for one, He can do it for me.

00:40:18.940 --> 00:40:32.300
If He can do it for that person, He can do it for you.

00:40:40.124 --> 00:40:40.613
He's no respecter of persons.

00:40:42.079 --> 00:41:00.640
And if you're listening to Him, even whenever your mind doesn't make sense of it—'I don't understand this in my natural mind'—the natural man perceiveth not the things of the Lord.

00:41:00.640 --> 00:41:03.473
I refuse to be carnally minded.

00:41:17.919 --> 00:41:18.319
I want to be spiritually led.

00:41:18.319 --> 00:41:22.240
God, lead me in everything I put my hands to.

00:41:22.240 --> 00:41:28.293
Help me, because in my natural self, I just barely got a GED.

00:41:36.000 --> 00:41:36.366
But I know that the men of the Bible were uneducated men, but they had been with Jesus.

00:41:36.366 --> 00:41:39.520
That's what made them stand out.

00:41:39.520 --> 00:41:50.800
What makes you stand out is that you've been with Jesus because He'll put His super on your natural if you would just allow Him.

00:41:50.800 --> 00:41:53.280
'Can I use you in these last days?

00:41:53.280 --> 00:41:55.380
' Here am I, Lord.

00:41:55.380 --> 00:41:56.391
Use me.

00:42:10.010 --> 00:42:10.260
All I've got is what You can use.

00:42:10.260 --> 00:42:11.260
This is it.

00:42:11.260 --> 00:42:16.297
You don't have much, but Lord, with what I have, You can use it.

00:42:33.383 --> 00:42:33.657
Do something with it.

00:42:34.206 --> 00:42:35.880
And He'll take whatever you've got.

00:42:35.880 --> 00:42:39.406
Like the widow lady who just barely had something.

00:42:39.406 --> 00:42:49.180
They just had the little bit of cornmeal and a little bit of oil to make a little cake, and they were going to die.

00:42:49.180 --> 00:42:53.170
But look what the man of God did.

00:43:15.711 --> 00:43:16.487
He blessed it.

00:43:16.487 --> 00:43:24.395
They fed it to him, and every pot filled with oil.

00:43:24.395 --> 00:43:34.896
They had all they could sell, and the blessing of the Lord was on it.

00:43:34.896 --> 00:43:41.440
Look at what God can do just with a little.

00:43:41.440 --> 00:43:45.960
He can turn it around and make it into much.

00:43:55.920 --> 00:43:56.080
I believe it's time to believe that the God of the Bible is the God of today.

00:43:56.080 --> 00:43:57.947
He has not changed.

00:44:00.640 --> 00:44:02.080
And what He did then—they didn't even have the covenant that we have.

00:44:13.040 --> 00:44:13.760
They were underneath the Abrahamic covenant.

00:44:15.410 --> 00:44:16.250
We have so much more.

00:44:16.250 --> 00:44:18.960
Jesus Christ dwells on the inside of you.

00:44:18.960 --> 00:44:22.300
He didn't dwell on the inside of them.

00:44:22.300 --> 00:44:23.599
We're wall-to-wall Holy Ghost.

00:44:35.760 --> 00:44:36.050
He dwells on the inside of us.

00:44:36.050 --> 00:44:38.755
As He is, so are we in this world.

00:44:38.755 --> 00:44:43.680
Now, we need to act like it and believe it.

00:44:52.860 --> 00:45:04.640
If He would do that for Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego; if He would do that for Daniel, Moses, Abraham, or Samson; how much more could He do it for you?

00:45:04.640 --> 00:45:16.445
We have the Holy Spirit that dwells on the inside of us richly by faith.

00:45:16.445 --> 00:45:23.440
How much more can He do through us if we just say, 'Yes, God, here am I'?

00:45:26.420 --> 00:45:26.640
I just think it's interesting.

00:45:26.640 --> 00:45:35.737
I was sitting there today and He said, 'Enlarge your capacity to believe Me for more, Brandon.

00:45:38.110 --> 00:45:38.420
You think too small.

00:45:38.420 --> 00:45:45.119
' I thought I was thinking big for what we're believing for.

00:45:45.119 --> 00:45:46.800
I'm supposed to believe God.

00:45:48.160 --> 00:45:52.960
And He said, 'You're still not believing Me for enough.

00:45:52.960 --> 00:45:56.436
' And to wrap my mind around what He's asking me for...

00:45:56.436 --> 00:46:01.240
He said, 'Don't you realize what we have to do in these last days?

00:46:01.240 --> 00:46:04.955
We're at the end of this.

00:46:09.710 --> 00:46:10.280
The sun is setting on this dispensation of grace.

00:46:20.410 --> 00:46:20.620
Do you realize I'm standing at the door and the bride is asleep?

00:46:20.620 --> 00:46:28.480
' Most of them have no urgency of My coming.

00:46:28.480 --> 00:46:32.187
It's time to rattle the cages.

00:46:32.187 --> 00:46:35.218
It's time to wake them up.

00:46:35.218 --> 00:46:36.284
I'm coming.

00:46:36.284 --> 00:46:41.680
It's like when He said to the disciples, 'Could you not just pray with Me for one hour?

00:46:43.422 --> 00:46:43.671
The hour is at hand.

00:46:43.671 --> 00:46:46.124
' I refuse to be asleep behind the wheel.

00:46:46.124 --> 00:46:50.230
Come on, wake up.

00:46:50.240 --> 00:47:07.300
So, I've said enough, but I tried to tell you what He's saying to me and just taking that step with Him of intimacy.

00:47:10.773 --> 00:47:10.960
You don't tell your secrets to somebody you don't trust.

00:47:16.391 --> 00:47:16.853
You tell your secrets to somebody that you're intimate with.

00:47:16.853 --> 00:47:19.253
Can God share His secrets with you?

00:47:19.253 --> 00:47:21.564
Are you intimate with Him?

00:47:29.440 --> 00:47:29.730
And that's what He said.

00:47:41.992 --> 00:47:42.224
You don't tell your secrets to anybody other than Dina because you're intimate with her.

00:47:42.224 --> 00:47:45.724
She's your friend; it's more than that—we have a covenant.

00:47:45.724 --> 00:47:52.373
There's nothing that she doesn't know about me, and there's nothing that I don't know about her.

00:47:52.373 --> 00:47:59.200
There is an intimacy in a marriage where you know everything about that individual.

00:48:05.138 --> 00:48:08.411
And that was what the Lord was saying to me: there's intimacy, and the more you're intimate with Me, I'll tell you the secret things.

00:48:19.851 --> 00:48:20.114
But I don't share intimacy with people who are not intimate with Me.

00:48:20.114 --> 00:48:23.184
Become intimate with Me and I will be intimate with you.

00:48:25.440 --> 00:48:26.720
I will show you that which is to come.

00:48:27.040 --> 00:48:29.090
You say, "Well, I don't hear Him.

00:48:29.090 --> 00:48:31.600
He doesn't talk to me about that kind of stuff.

00:48:31.600 --> 00:48:33.120
Are you any better than me, Brent?

00:48:33.120 --> 00:48:34.080
" No, no, no.

00:48:34.080 --> 00:48:35.840
My decisions have been different.

00:48:35.840 --> 00:48:39.431
Maybe my walk with the Lord has been different.

00:48:54.700 --> 00:48:54.870
I don't know the time you spend with Him.

00:48:58.612 --> 00:49:00.139
I don't try to say, "Well, I'm self-righteous; I spend all these hours a day.

00:49:00.139 --> 00:49:02.090
" No, it's quality time.

00:49:02.090 --> 00:49:03.060
It's intimacy.

00:49:03.060 --> 00:49:05.931
It's allowing Him in your thought pattern.

00:49:05.931 --> 00:49:14.720
It's allowing Him into your inner circle and inviting Him daily, not just every once in a while.

00:49:30.409 --> 00:49:30.711
And it's obeying Him even whenever your flesh doesn't want to.

00:49:30.711 --> 00:49:41.359
Your flesh will scream whenever He tells you to give certain things away and do certain things, and you'll go, "I will not do this.

00:49:57.348 --> 00:49:57.531
" But it's being faithful with little, and He'll make you ruler over much.

00:49:57.531 --> 00:50:06.280
Whenever you're faithful with the small thing, God will bless you with the bigger thing.

00:50:10.880 --> 00:50:11.200
But until you become faithful with the little, don't you ask Him for more?

00:50:11.200 --> 00:50:16.126
People always ask Him, "Well, how come I can't go from here to there?

00:50:31.200 --> 00:50:31.867
" It starts out with just five dollars.

00:50:31.867 --> 00:50:35.982
Can you be obedient with a dollar?

00:50:35.982 --> 00:50:39.653
Can you be obedient with a hundred dollars?

00:50:39.653 --> 00:50:45.240
If you cannot be obedient with a dollar, how does He take you to a hundred dollars?

00:50:45.240 --> 00:50:52.666
He will not share His secret things with people He cannot trust.

00:50:52.666 --> 00:51:03.270
Prove yourself trustworthy in these last days, and He will show you the secret things and the hidden things.

00:51:15.360 --> 00:51:15.759
Be faithful with what He's given you, honor it, and take care of it.

00:51:15.759 --> 00:51:31.319
I don't know how many times I would take our clunky car to the car wash and wax a car with the paint coming off or wrecked.

00:51:50.053 --> 00:51:50.387
People said, "Why don't you replace that bumper?

00:51:50.387 --> 00:51:54.692
" I didn't have the money to.

00:51:59.428 --> 00:51:59.851
The bumper was falling off of our Honda Accord, and we didn't have the money to fix it.

00:52:13.119 --> 00:52:13.440
We had it zip-tied.

00:52:14.400 --> 00:52:15.680
We fixed that thing with Diana.

00:52:15.680 --> 00:52:22.720
But I always waxed and took care of that car falling apart.

00:52:22.720 --> 00:52:31.560
Even when they repoed it because we couldn't make our payments, they took it from us.

00:52:31.560 --> 00:52:49.739
It was falling apart, and I remember they came—and it's bad when you get a car repoed from you when the front bumper's off and there's so much stuff going on with it—but I kept it clean.

00:52:59.475 --> 00:52:59.804
And when they came up there and took it, I kept it clean.

00:53:00.790 --> 00:53:03.748
And the guy goes, "Man, he took care of it.

00:53:04.982 --> 00:53:05.291
You tried.

00:53:05.291 --> 00:53:07.249
" Amen.

00:53:07.249 --> 00:53:15.440
Even whenever the bank came in and took it from us, I took care of it.

00:53:15.440 --> 00:53:20.230
You've been faithful even with what God's given you.

00:53:30.960 --> 00:53:31.732
Even if it's not that nice, you always take care of it.

00:53:46.080 --> 00:53:46.320
And when you borrow somebody else's car, you make sure it's full of gas and clean when you return it.

00:53:46.320 --> 00:53:52.195
Don't return it dirty and with an empty tank of gas.

00:53:52.195 --> 00:53:59.670
Always do good unto others.

00:53:59.680 --> 00:54:10.790
Bless them.

00:54:19.613 --> 00:54:19.929
And that's what we've always tried to do.

00:54:19.929 --> 00:54:27.645
If Grandma ever lent us her van, I always made sure it was clean, vacuumed out, and full of gas when I returned it.

00:54:27.645 --> 00:54:28.059
Always.

00:54:28.059 --> 00:54:30.293
More gas than when we got it.

00:54:30.293 --> 00:54:30.986
Yes.

00:54:30.986 --> 00:54:37.656
Always treating people with respect when it comes to borrowing their stuff and honoring it when you get it.

00:54:37.656 --> 00:54:41.560
Don't return it back broken and don't return it back dirty.

00:54:41.560 --> 00:54:44.115
When you go into somebody's hotel room, don't leave it trashed.

00:54:50.782 --> 00:54:51.031
I always think somebody's going to have to come in here and clean this up.

00:55:00.980 --> 00:55:01.210
I clean it before they—hey, it was always nice and clean and not trashed.

00:55:09.320 --> 00:55:09.550
You go in there and don't steal their towels.

00:55:09.550 --> 00:55:10.816
"Well, you know what?

00:55:17.440 --> 00:55:18.133
I'm going to take the towel.

00:55:18.133 --> 00:55:19.520
" No.

00:55:19.520 --> 00:55:20.297
Or the robe.

00:55:26.000 --> 00:55:26.347
You honor where you go.

00:55:26.347 --> 00:55:28.772
Show God wherever you go.

00:55:28.772 --> 00:55:29.539
Show people.

00:55:29.539 --> 00:55:31.493
That's what I try to do everywhere.

00:55:31.493 --> 00:55:32.187
Have integrity.

00:55:32.187 --> 00:55:35.050
Clean the church as if Jesus Himself was walking in there.

00:55:35.050 --> 00:55:37.386
Do it unto the Lord.

00:55:37.386 --> 00:55:39.359
And continue to do it.

00:55:39.359 --> 00:55:41.1000
Whatever you do, do unto God.

00:55:41.1000 --> 00:55:45.099
I did it every single time with everything.

00:55:45.099 --> 00:55:55.095
When you mow somebody's yard and they couldn't take care of it, I made it look like it was the best.

00:55:55.095 --> 00:56:01.030
Who's going to come?

00:56:01.040 --> 00:56:07.866
And I want it to look the best when they show up.

00:56:07.866 --> 00:56:08.666
Have integrity.

00:56:08.666 --> 00:56:15.253
Even mowing grass, pulling weeds, whatever you can do, have excellence in doing it.

00:56:15.253 --> 00:56:16.739
Cleanliness is godliness, you know.

